He's partially paralysed but that hasn't stopped Oom Rowland Williams from Cape Town from becoming a flower king. JOHANNESBURG - He's partially paralysed but that hasn't stopped a Cape Town man from becoming a flower king. Oom Rowland Williams had a severe stroke but has become a household name in his hometown of Pniel. Twenty-one years ago, doctors said he would never walk or talk again, but today, 72-year-old, Williams, has proved them wrong. And that's partly thanks to finding strength and healing through gardening. On National Garden Day, eNCA's Tanya Nefdt joins him as he reflects on how gardening has helped him survive. Watch the video above.